29/10/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Warplanes bombed bases of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in northern Iraq on Tuesday (October 28th), the Turkish General Staff said on its website.
The jets struck PKK targets in the regions of Hakurk, Avasin-Basyan and Zap, backed by artillery fire from Turkey.
The raid neither targeted nor hit any civilians, the statement added.
(Zaman, Hurriyet, NTV, CNN Turk, AFP - 28/10/08)
